# Backend Development Rules

## Stack
Python 3.12, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2 (async), Alembic, Pydantic v2, scapy, python-jose (JWT), authlib (OAuth), httpx, OpenAI SDK, aiofiles, python-multipart, itsdangerous, psycopg2-binary (Alembic sync driver).

## Database
- All database access goes through `async_session` from `app.db.session`.
- Use the `async with async_session() as session:` pattern.
- Models live in `app/models/`, schemas in `app/schemas/`.
- `Base` is defined in `app.db.session`; import `app.models` to register all tables.
- Enum types use `str, enum.Enum` + `SAEnum` for PostgreSQL compatibility.
- Alembic migrations use a synchronous driver; `env.py` strips `+asyncpg`/`+psycopg_async` from `DATABASE_URL`.

## API Routes
- Prefixes: `/api/captures`, `/auth`, `/api/health`.
- Dependencies: `get_current_user` for auth; routes open their own `async_session()` context for DB access.
- Uploads: `POST /api/captures` — validates extensions (.pcap, .pcapng, .cap) and pcap magic bytes, streams to a temp file, enforces `max_upload_bytes`, creates the DB record, and spawns `parse_pcap` as a background task.
- Captures: `GET /api/captures` lists with pagination; `GET /api/captures/{id}` reads one; `DELETE /api/captures/{id}` removes the DB row and best-effort filesystem sidecars (`.jsonl`, `.index.json`) plus evicts the in-memory index cache.
- Packets: `GET /api/captures/{id}/packets` reads `index.json`, supports `?proto=`, `?offset=`, `?limit=` (default 200, max 10000, filter applies to total). `GET /api/captures/{id}/packets/{packet_idx}` returns full detail from `.jsonl`.
- Statistics: `GET /api/captures/{id}/statistics` — aggregates from conversations; query params `bucket_seconds` (snaps to `{1, 10, 30, 60}` seconds) and `metric` (`packets` or `bytes`).
- Analysis: `GET /api/captures/{id}/ai` — SSE streaming; aborts if the client disconnects; persists only successful analyses.

## Models (`app/models/capture.py`)
- `Capture`: id, user_id, filename, size_bytes, sha256, linktype (default 1), packet_count, status (`CaptureStatus` enum), stored_path, parsed_index_path, created_at.
- `Conversation`: id, capture_id, proto, src_ip, src_port, dst_ip, dst_port, packet_count, byte_count, start_ts, end_ts, app_protocol, flags_summary (comma-separated TCP flag names, e.g. `SYN,ACK`).
- `Analysis`: id, conversation_id, model, prompt_tokens, completion_tokens, summary_markdown, issues_json, created_at.

## Models (`app/models/user.py`)
- `User`: id, github_id (unique), login, email, name, avatar_url, created_at.

## Pcap Parser (`app/services/pcap_parser.py`)
- `parse_pcap(capture_id)` — background task, offloaded via `asyncio.to_thread`.
- Uses `scapy.utils.PcapReader` (streaming).
- Writes `capture_id.jsonl` (per-packet records) + `capture_id.index.json` (byte offsets + summaries for O(1) random access).
- Calls `build_conversations()` from `app/services/flows.py`.
- Updates capture status: uploaded -> parsing -> ready/failed.
- Application protocol detection is centralized here (`_TCP_PORT_PROTOCOLS`, `_UDP_PORT_PROTOCOLS`) and mirrors `wiki/Uploading-and-Analyzing.md`.

## Packet Index Cache (`app/api/packets.py`)
- `packets.py` keeps an in-memory LRU cache of parsed `index.json` files keyed by `(path, mtime_ns, size)`.
- `_evict_index()` is called on capture deletion so re-uploads never surface stale indices.

## Startup Recovery (`app/main.py`)
- On startup `_reset_stuck_captures()` flips any capture still in `parsing` status to `failed`, because FastAPI BackgroundTasks do not survive a worker restart.

## Settings (`app/config.py`)
- Pydantic `BaseSettings` with `.env` file support, `extra="ignore"`.
- Security knobs: `dev_mode` (relaxes secret validation; never in production), `cookie_secure` (default true), `session_secret` (fallback to JWT_SECRET in dev), `jwt_expire_minutes`.
- Insecure defaults (`CHANGE_ME`, empty, etc.) raise on startup unless `dev_mode=true`.

## Standalone Frontend Serving (`app/main.py`)
- When `SERVE_FRONTEND=true` and `FRONTEND_DIR` (default `/app/frontend-dist`) exists, the built SPA is mounted via `StaticFiles(directory=_FRONTEND_DIR, html=True)` at `/`.
- API/auth routes take priority.

## Key Dependencies
```
fastapi, uvicorn, sqlalchemy[asyncio], asyncpg, alembic, pydantic-settings
scapy, python-jose[cryptography], authlib, httpx, openai, python-multipart,
aiofiles, itsdangerous, psycopg2-binary
```
